<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n22064l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22064l">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22064l"> 64(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Shifty son / masterthief</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Gaelic &ldquo;Tales of the Shifty Lad, the Widow&apos;s Son&rdquo;, among many others, is derived from the &ldquo;Dolopathos&rdquo;. It corresponds closely with the Norwegian version of the tale of &ldquo;Mestertyven&rdquo; (the Master-thief) from Kvindherred in Hardanger. <small> Alexander Bugge, <a name="ABUG" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ABUG"><cite title="source">Contributions to the History of the Norsemen in Ireland</cite></a> (1900) II, 27</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05218f" href="c05all.htm#c05218f">VI.C.05:218(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
